<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P N="340">(340-345.) In all Sy&s;tems of Super&s;tition there have ever been mingled &s;ome Seeds of TRUTH, which during the Growth and Prevalence of it, like Corn among Weeds, are lo&s;t, and &s;mo|thered; but as that decays, the&s;e ri&s;e and flouri&s;h. TRUTH be|ing of a permanent Nature, and &s;uper&s;tition variable, when the former prevails, the Mind is inlightened with Knowledge, and the Heart warmed with Benevolence and natural Affection. This Light and Warmth melts away the Phantoms of Super&s;tition&mdash;
